  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The majority of lung cancer patients have a tumor-derived genetic alteration in circulating
      plasma DNA that could be exploited as a diagnostic tool. The aim of this study is to evaluate
      if plasma DNA can be used as a valuable non invasive test to monitor disease progression
      without assessing the tumor.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
